This paper discusses the ability of modern computers to handle large volumes of financial transactions, which falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), software engineering (cs.SE), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the specific mention of debit/credit transactions suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and financial technology (FinTech).
